http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/Green-corridor-saves-life-again/article14000189.ece

Two green corridors were set up in the city on Thursday to facilitate organ transportation to the All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS), saving the life of a 23-year-old from Haryana.“A potential multi-organ donor was reported from PGI Chandigarh on January 14 morning. The hospital gave a call to AIIMS told them about the heart available. For the transportation of the heart and liver the Indian Air Force provided support and after the organs reached Palam airport green corridors were provided by the Traffic Police to the Research and Referral Hospital and later to AIIMS,” noted a release issued by AIIMS.It added that this is the first time public hospitals initiated this level of coordination for saving a life.